.TH PODCTLD 1 "2026" "podctl 0.1.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
podctld \- AirPods control daemon
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B podctld
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B podctld
is the long-running companion daemon for the
.BR podctl (1)
CLI. It holds the persistent state of the user's AirPods: the BlueZ
device link, the L2CAP Apple Accessory Protocol channel, the audio
output state, and a broadcast bus of live events that subscribed
clients (e.g.
.B podctl watch
) consume.
.PP
The daemon listens on a per-user Unix-domain stream socket at
.IR $XDG_RUNTIME_DIR/podctl.sock ,
mode
.IR 0600 .
Requests are newline-delimited JSON; one request normally produces one
response, except for
.BR watch ,
which produces a stream until the client disconnects.
.PP
.B podctld
is optional. When it is not running,
.BR podctl (1)
falls back to a standalone path that handles audio and basic Bluetooth
operations directly; live state (battery, in-ear, button events) and
the
.B watch
subscription require the daemon.
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B RUST_LOG
Log level filter (default
.IR info ).
Examples:
.BR debug ,
.BR "info,podctld=trace" .
.TP
.B XDG_RUNTIME_DIR
Directory for the socket (default
.IR /run/user/$UID ).
.SH SIGNALS
.TP
.B SIGTERM, SIGINT
Initiate graceful shutdown: drain in-flight requests, remove the socket
file, exit 0.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I $XDG_RUNTIME_DIR/podctl.sock
The control socket.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR podctl (1),
.BR systemd.unit (5).
